{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1d10a91-0002-4000-8000-000000000010",
    "name": "Audio API",
    "description": "Audio analysis API.\n\n**Tenant API** — file-based Jobs (format / VAD / language / D-M-E classify) and live Streams (subtitles). Authenticated with a tenant token (`{{token}}`).\n\n**Admin API** — cross-tenant operator surface for the ops console: streams, jobs, pods, tenants, tokens and operator-adjustable settings. Off unless the gateway runs with `ADMIN_API_ENABLED=1`. Authenticated with an admin token (`{{admin_token}}`) from `make seed-admin` — a tenant token is rejected here.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection AND `audio-api.postman_environment.json`.\n2. Select the `Audio API (local)` environment.\n3. `token` defaults to the dev tenant seed. Set `admin_token` to your admin token (`make seed-admin`, or the `ADMIN_API_TOKEN` in the console's `.env.local`).\n4. Requests auto-save returned IDs (`job_id`, `stream_id`, `token_id`) into the environment, so follow-ups resolve `{{job_id}}` / `{{stream_id}}` without copy-paste.\n\n## WebSocket\n`Stream captions (WS)` is a WebSocket. Create a real WS request in Postman from that URL; auth uses the same `{{token}}`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "{{base_url}}", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "ws_url", "value": "{{ws_url}}", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/health",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/health", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "health"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Jobs",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/jobs  (async, all analyses)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status 200/201/202', () => pm.expect([200, 201, 202]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (body && body.job_id) { pm.environment.set('job_id', body.job_id); console.log('saved job_id =', body.job_id); }"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"input\": { \"type\": \"url\", \"url\": \"https://example.com/sample.wav\" },\n  \"analyses\": [\"format\", \"vad\", \"language\", \"dme_classify\"],\n  \"options\": {\n    \"language\": { \"candidates\": [\"en\", \"fr\", \"de\"] },\n    \"dme_classify\": { \"segment_ms\": 1000 }\n  },\n  \"mode\": \"async\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/jobs", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "jobs"] },
            "description": "Submit a job. `mode: async` returns 201 immediately. `mode: sync` blocks up to SYNC_TIMEOUT_MS (default 60s); on timeout returns 202 with job_id so you can poll. Saves `job_id` to the environment."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/jobs  (sync, format only)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (body && body.job_id) pm.environment.set('job_id', body.job_id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"input\": { \"type\": \"url\", \"url\": \"https://example.com/short.wav\" },\n  \"analyses\": [\"format\"],\n  \"mode\": \"sync\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/jobs", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "jobs"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/jobs/{{job_id}}",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/jobs/{{job_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "jobs", "{{job_id}}"] },
            "description": "Job status + per-analysis progress."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/jobs/{{job_id}}/results",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/jobs/{{job_id}}/results", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "jobs", "{{job_id}}", "results"] },
            "description": "Aggregated report. 404 until the job completes."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Streams (live subtitles)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/streams  (hls)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (body.stream_id) pm.environment.set('stream_id', body.stream_id);",
                  "if (body.outputs && body.outputs.websocket_url) pm.environment.set('stream_ws_url', body.outputs.websocket_url);",
                  "console.log('saved stream_id =', body.stream_id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"source\": { \"kind\": \"hls\", \"url\": \"https://dwamdstream102.akamaized.net/hls/live/2015525/dwstream102/index.m3u8\" },\n  \"source_hint\": \"de\",\n  \"output\": { \"target_lang\": \"en\" },\n  \"options\": { \"model_size\": \"small\" }\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/streams", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "streams"] },
            "description": "Provisions a stream-pod for the source. `source.kind` is one of `hls|dash|mp4|srt`. `source.url` must be `https` (set `STREAM_ALLOW_HTTP=1` to allow `http`). Response includes `outputs.websocket_url` (live cues) and `outputs.vtt_url`. Saves `stream_id` and `stream_ws_url`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/streams  (srt caller)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"source\": {\n    \"kind\": \"srt\",\n    \"url\": \"srt://encoder.example.com:9000\",\n    \"mode\": \"caller\",\n    \"passphrase\": \"your-passphrase\"\n  },\n  \"output\": { \"target_lang\": \"en\" }\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/streams", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "streams"] },
            "description": "srt caller: the pod dials out to your SRT server, no inbound ports. `passphrase` optional, 10-64 chars, sealed at rest and never echoed back."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/streams  (srt listener)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"source\": {\n    \"kind\": \"srt\",\n    \"mode\": \"listener\",\n    \"passphrase\": \"your-passphrase\"\n  },\n  \"output\": { \"target_lang\": \"en\" }\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/streams", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "streams"] },
            "description": "srt listener: your encoder pushes into the pod. Omit `source.url` (sending one is a 400). Poll GET /v1/streams/{id} for the concrete `srt://host:port` ingest endpoint before pointing your encoder at it. `passphrase` required here."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/streams/{{stream_id}}",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/streams/{{stream_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "streams", "{{stream_id}}"] },
            "description": "Status: provisioning -> awaiting_ingest -> active -> ending -> ended -> archived (or failed)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "DELETE /v1/streams/{{stream_id}}",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/streams/{{stream_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "streams", "{{stream_id}}"] },
            "description": "Ends the stream. Gateway flips status to `ending` and the supervisor SIGTERMs the pod."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Stream captions (WS)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{ws_url}}/v1/streams/{{stream_id}}/captions", "host": ["{{ws_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "streams", "{{stream_id}}", "captions"] },
            "description": "**WebSocket.** In Postman: New -> WebSocket Request -> paste this URL -> header `Authorization: Bearer {{token}}` -> Connect. Cues arrive as JSON messages."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Admin",
      "description": "Cross-tenant operator API. Requires the gateway to run with ADMIN_API_ENABLED=1 and a Bearer admin token in {{admin_token}}. A tenant token is rejected by every route here.",
      "auth": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{admin_token}}", "type": "string" }]
      },
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Settings",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/settings",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/settings", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "settings"] },
                "description": "Operator-adjustable pod tuning. Each setting reports { value, default, effective, source }: `value` is the database override (null when unset), `default` is the deployment env value, `effective` = value ?? default, `source` is `database` or `environment`. Changes apply to new streams only."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "PUT /v1/admin/settings  (set max duration = 300s)",
              "request": {
                "method": "PUT",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"pod_max_duration_s\": 300\n}" },
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/settings", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "settings"] },
                "description": "Partial update. Absent key = leave alone. Returns the full settings in the same shape as GET. Writes a settings.update audit row."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "PUT /v1/admin/settings  (No limit: max duration = 0)",
              "request": {
                "method": "PUT",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"pod_max_duration_s\": 0\n}" },
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/settings", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "settings"] },
                "description": "0 = unlimited. A stream with no cap holds a GPU until something else ends it."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "PUT /v1/admin/settings  (multiple + reset one to default)",
              "request": {
                "method": "PUT",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"pod_idle_timeout_s\": 45,\n  \"pod_model_size\": \"medium\",\n  \"pod_max_duration_s\": null\n}" },
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/settings", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "settings"] },
                "description": "Explicit null unsets a setting, reverting it to the environment default. Here: set idle timeout + model, revert max duration. pod_model_size is one of tiny|base|small|medium|large-v3."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "PUT /v1/admin/settings  (invalid -> 400)",
              "request": {
                "method": "PUT",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"pod_max_duration_s\": -1\n}" },
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/settings", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "settings"] },
                "description": "Rejected with ADMIN_INVALID_QUERY. Also rejects unknown keys, non-integers, and an unknown model size."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Streams",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/streams",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/streams?limit=50",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["v1", "admin", "streams"],
                  "query": [
                    { "key": "status", "value": "active", "disabled": true },
                    { "key": "tenant_id", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                    { "key": "limit", "value": "50" },
                    { "key": "cursor", "value": "", "disabled": true }
                  ]
                },
                "description": "Cross-tenant list, newest first. Optional filters: status, tenant_id. Keyset paging via cursor/next_cursor."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/streams/{{stream_id}}",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/streams/{{stream_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "streams", "{{stream_id}}"] },
                "description": "Stream detail plus the pod it landed on (included even when stale; null if unassigned)."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/streams/{{stream_id}}/cues",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/streams/{{stream_id}}/cues?limit=50",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["v1", "admin", "streams", "{{stream_id}}", "cues"],
                  "query": [
                    { "key": "since", "value": "0", "disabled": true },
                    { "key": "limit", "value": "50" }
                  ]
                },
                "description": "Caption feed, ascending. Poll with `since` = the last cue_id seen. The first read (since < 0 / absent) is audited."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "POST /v1/admin/streams/{{stream_id}}/kill",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"reason\": \"operator kill from Postman\"\n}" },
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/streams/{{stream_id}}/kill", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "streams", "{{stream_id}}", "kill"] },
                "description": "Operator kill switch. 202 -> status `ending`. 404 wrong id, ADMIN_INVALID_STATE if already finished. `reason` is recorded in the audit log."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Jobs",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/jobs",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/jobs?limit=50",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["v1", "admin", "jobs"],
                  "query": [
                    { "key": "status", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                    { "key": "tenant_id", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                    { "key": "limit", "value": "50" }
                  ]
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/jobs/{{job_id}}",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/jobs/{{job_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "jobs", "{{job_id}}"] },
                "description": "Job detail with its analyses."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/jobs/{{job_id}}/results",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/jobs/{{job_id}}/results", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "jobs", "{{job_id}}", "results"] }
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/jobs/{{job_id}}/events",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/jobs/{{job_id}}/events", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "jobs", "{{job_id}}", "events"] },
                "description": "Event timeline. Worker-written payloads have URLs recursively redacted."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Pods",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/pods",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/pods?settled=false&limit=200",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["v1", "admin", "pods"],
                  "query": [
                    { "key": "settled", "value": "false", "description": "false hides dead/terminated pods" },
                    { "key": "stale", "value": "true", "disabled": true },
                    { "key": "status", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                    { "key": "limit", "value": "200" }
                  ]
                },
                "description": "GPU pod fleet with heartbeat age + a computed `stale` flag."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Tenants",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/tenants",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/tenants", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "tenants"] },
                "description": "Derived tenant list with job/stream/token counts and last activity."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Tokens",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "GET /v1/admin/tokens",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/tokens?tenant_id={{tenant_id}}",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["v1", "admin", "tokens"],
                  "query": [{ "key": "tenant_id", "value": "{{tenant_id}}" }]
                },
                "description": "Tenant API tokens (never the hash or plaintext). Drop tenant_id to list all."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "POST /v1/admin/tokens  (issue)",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "type": "text/javascript",
                    "exec": [
                      "const body = pm.response.json();",
                      "if (body && body.id) pm.environment.set('token_id', body.id);",
                      "if (body && body.token) console.log('PLAINTEXT (shown once):', body.token);"
                    ]
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"tenant_id\": \"{{tenant_id}}\",\n  \"name\": \"issued from Postman\",\n  \"allow_new_tenant\": false\n}" },
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/tokens", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "tokens"] },
                "description": "Issue a tenant token. The plaintext is returned exactly once (logged to the Postman console by the test script). For a brand-new tenant, set allow_new_tenant: true. Saves the row id to {{token_id}}."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "POST /v1/admin/tokens/{{token_id}}/revoke",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [],
                "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/tokens/{{token_id}}/revoke", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "tokens", "{{token_id}}", "revoke"] },
                "description": "Idempotent. Revoking an already-revoked token does not rewrite when access ended."
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Negative / auth cases",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/streams  (no auth -> 401)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"source\": { \"kind\": \"hls\", \"url\": \"https://fixtures.invalid/skeleton.m3u8\" },\n  \"output\": { \"target_lang\": \"en\" }\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/streams", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "streams"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/admin/settings  (tenant token -> 401)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }] },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/admin/settings", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "admin", "settings"] },
            "description": "A tenant token is not an admin token. Every /v1/admin route rejects it (ADMIN_AUTH_FAILED). Also 404 for the whole surface if the gateway runs without ADMIN_API_ENABLED=1."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/streams  (unsupported source.kind -> 400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"source\": { \"kind\": \"rtmp\", \"url\": \"rtmp://x/y\" },\n  \"output\": { \"target_lang\": \"en\" }\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/streams", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "streams"] },
            "description": "source.kind must be one of hls|dash|mp4|srt."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/streams/s_doesnotexist  (-> 404)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/streams/s_doesnotexist", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "streams", "s_doesnotexist"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
